<i>noun</i>: 시문 [시문], 문헌 [문헌], 문학 [문학], 문예 [무녜] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>시문 [시문]</dt><br>
<dd>literature; literary works</dd><br>
<dd>시와 산문.</dd><br>
<dd>Poetry and prose.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>문헌 [문헌]</dt><br>
<dd>1. literature; document</dd><br>
<dd>옛날의 제도나 문물을 아는 데 증거가 되는 자료나 기록.</dd><br>
<dd>Material or record that serves as evidence for understanding an institution or culture of the past.</dd><br>
<dd>2. reference</dd><br>
<dd>연구의 자료가 되는 책이나 문서.</dd><br>
<dd>A book or document that serves as the material for research.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>문학 [문학]</dt><br>
<dd>literature</dd><br>
<dd>시, 소설, 수필, 희곡 등과 같이 사람의 생각이나 감정을 말이나 글로 표현한 예술.</dd><br>
<dd>An art that expresses people's thoughts or emotions through words or writings such as poems, novels, essays, plays, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>문예 [무녜]</dt><br>
<dd>1. literature and art</dd><br>
<dd>문학과 예술.</dd><br>
<dd>A compound noun meaning literature and art.</dd><br>
<dd>2. literature</dd><br>
<dd>예술로서의 문학.</dd><br>
<dd>Literature as part of art.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>